website_summaries.verdict: Great set to buy if you and your friends want to give disc golf a try.
pros: Discs include 3 each of drivers, mid-range discs, and putters
Each disc is color-coded for easy identification
Ships with a carrying case for all 9 discs
cons: Only usable for the novice player, not for those with experience

customer_reviews.title: THE Family Disc Golf Starter Set.
customer_reviews.text: Driver, mid, and putter emulate shapes of the brand name discs, and fly well. As reviewed elsewhere, these look and act like "DX" plastic. So you are getting discs that are essentially the same as the name brands "DX" line of discs for less than half the cost. Perfect for my family of 6 where we needed lots of discs. Can personalize the blank tops with permanent marker. Can buff out scratches and chips with scraps of carpet. Bag is fine for storing them. Very happy with purchase. Disc weights were consistent between the 3 types: Red Mid Range: 147grams Yellow Driver: 156g Blue Putter: 164g
customer_reviews.author: coolredspkrguy

customer_reviews.title: This set gave us the most fun round we've had in a long time
customer_reviews.text: Bought these to split between my friends and myself for the occasional "starter pack challenge" round. My friends and I have all been playing for roughly one year. This set gave us the most fun round we've had in a long time, and these discs are good enough that they could actually find slots in our regular bags. If nothing else, it was gonna be interesting to play completely blind with these cheap, unbranded, unknown discs, so them being great to play with, even regularly, was a pleasant cherry on top. 5 stars for extremely high bang-for-buck.
customer_reviews.author: Namaztak

customer_reviews.title: They will work, but not well
customer_reviews.text: I bought these for our youth group to have a few sets of discs available to students without them. They are sturdy and durable but several came slightly warped. They are heavy and don't fly great, but they are inexpensive and work for their purposes.
customer_reviews.author: Jamie

customer_reviews.title: Great for new players
customer_reviews.text: Recently got into disc golf, I bought this thinking it would be good for me. Turns out I’m addicted to buying new disc. So I don’t really use this set. But it is great for taking other people or kids out that have never played. The down side is all the drivers are the same color and the same for the mids and the putters. People looking for there disc can’t tell which one they threw, so I spray painted them different colors.
customer_reviews.author: mathew w steed

customer_reviews.title: Ok at best
customer_reviews.text: I have been playing disk gold for several years and bought this for my nephews to take them out as a group. Color description did not match disk type. Also had 3 putters and 6 drivers or mid range... the blue and red were identical. The yellow were putter design. Quality was low with some warping of disk and sharp edges where it was molded. Ok only for basic intro only. If you can afford any other intro set like one from innovo, buy that .
customer_reviews.author: Jamie Thompson

customer_reviews.title: Good for beginners
customer_reviews.text: I've never played disc golf before, but a friend of ours had. He told us the difference between the three color frisbees (they're not labeled, so we had to go off what our friend said each one was used for). One of them broke while we were playing, but out of all of the items I looked for, this was the best value. If we get more into disc golf, I'll buy a more expensive set.
customer_reviews.author: Rachael

customer_reviews.title: Ugh
customer_reviews.text: Product itself was good except the carry bag had mold or something on it.
customer_reviews.author: ashly

customer_reviews.title: Not horrible - no regerts
customer_reviews.text: Drivers: +fun to throw +yellow, and basically impossible to find in tall grass or woods Mid-range: +absolutely worthless Putter: +also quite fun to throw I would give this set 4 stars if the drivers were orange or red. I only have one left. Also, I would give it 5 stars the mid-range discs were any more useful. Overall, I don't regret buying this set, but I'm also glad I bought some better discs.
customer_reviews.author: Bret

customer_reviews.title: Good starter set, but damage easily
customer_reviews.text: This is a good disc golf set for beginners who want enough discs to play a game with others. The main problem with these is that they dent and chip easy and after one round, will look well used. This does not seem to happen with our friends discs they bought individually and locally. They work well, but just do not look good.
customer_reviews.author: Jaxterp

customer_reviews.title: Fun Fun Fun ...
customer_reviews.text: I am by no means an expert on disc golf, but I am an expert on FUN! My wife, kids, sister, brother-in-law, nephews and brother all had a GREAT time with these. They seemed to work as intended. Great to have a bag and 9 discs.
customer_reviews.author: Mano

customer_reviews.title: These are pretty good.
customer_reviews.text: Me and my buddies are new to disc golf and this is a good starter kit. I was expecting very cheap plastic and underwhelming performance, but these discs are made pretty decently and perform great.
customer_reviews.author: Mr. Douglas

customer_reviews.title: This is a great set of discs
customer_reviews.text: This is a great set of discs. These are ideal for beginners. None of these discs have any fancy logos or markings on them, but you will not be disappointed in their performance. The yellow discs are for long-range, the orange discs are for mid-range, and the blue ones are for putting. Again, you will find this set is ideal for beginners working their way towards buying some more expensive discs in the future after you get where you don't lose every one of them, LOL
customer_reviews.author: Gimpdog

customer_reviews.title: Great for beginers
customer_reviews.text: Since these discs get beat up, this is a great way to start. Not as well made as brand names, but they seem to fly just fine. The case is cheap and won't likely hold up, but is a nice bonus.
customer_reviews.author: S. C.

customer_reviews.title: Used for P.E. class
customer_reviews.text: This was a great product. I bought a couple of the packs. I see over 150 students a day. Some of them did get beat up a little bit, but overall they held up nicely.
customer_reviews.author: Anthony

customer_reviews.title: Great value, and great for households.
customer_reviews.text: I loved these discs! Some reviews say they're not flying straight, but from what I could tell as a beginner, we could get them going relatively straight with some practice. Love the value of them and having a 3 sets of 3. Only minor gripe is no indication of which color is for what, although you learn. For those that need, blue is your putter, red is mid range, and yellow is the driver.
customer_reviews.author: Casey Robinson

customer_reviews.title: Great buy for a family
customer_reviews.text: A group of colleagues bagged me into playing disk golf with them one afternoon, and I actually ended up liking it...being in the outdoors with friends, just enjoying the little things that makes life worth living. I bought the set cuz I was going to nag others to come out and play too. Lol
customer_reviews.author: Marcus K. Tambwe

customer_reviews.title: Great for someone getting into disc golf.
customer_reviews.text: These’s are great practice discs for someone just getting into disc golf. They are well-made. The bag that holds the desk is well-made too. I bought one for my car to take with me when I practice. My wife used them and wanted a set too.
customer_reviews.author: STEVEN P GESSNER

customer_reviews.title: Good for a small group of beginners
customer_reviews.text: I got this so I would have a starter set and have some in case some friends wanted to play. They are cheap, light pieces of plastic that I really wouldn't recommend to anyone who wants to play more than once. In this case "for beginners" is an apt way to describe a set that is cheaply made. Disclaimer: I played disc golf once before and I know how to throw a disc but I would still call myself a beginner.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Good for skeet practice?
customer_reviews.text: Unless your preteens are disc golfing, pass. Great to lose in the woods without fretting. About the upside of these rubber hubcaps.
customer_reviews.author: Jejmoe

customer_reviews.title: 3 identical sets u need to mark them to distinguish
customer_reviews.text: Price is right. Can use sharpie to distinguish the sets. I have virtually no experience but the sucks flew a long way.
customer_reviews.author: robot 33

customer_reviews.title: Solid value for the beginner (s)
customer_reviews.text: Solid set for beginners. Even space to decorate them for those youngans your looking to bring into the sport. We named each one and he drew a picture on the top. Don't stand up well to trees but that is with a high velocity throw... Perfect for beginners.
customer_reviews.author: Jordan Barnes

customer_reviews.title: I like them
customer_reviews.text: I decided to get these when I could no longer get the 3-pack I had been using. I'm a beginner and one course is brutal. I really like them. They seem to fly a bit straighter than the ones I had been using, especially the putter. I'd definitely buy them again and, unfortunately, probably will have to.
customer_reviews.author: brian

customer_reviews.title: Durable, great for kids
customer_reviews.text: Very good introductory set of discs. Bought them to use at home during or mandatory stay-cay and they've definitely taken a beating but keep on flying.
customer_reviews.author: Alaina E.

customer_reviews.title: Good Starter Kit
customer_reviews.text: Great starter kit. These do not feel like frisbees and there is an art to throwing them, but once you have that down they are really fun to play with. The whole family enjoyed our introduction to disc golf with these, even the not usually sporty child.
customer_reviews.author: AJ Dowda

customer_reviews.title: Family fun
customer_reviews.text: From my limited knowledge about disc golf discs, these seem fine. I generally don't get a ton of difference between the 3 types of discs, but it might just be technique. They scuff easily when they hit objects, like trees and rocks. The carry case is convenient. Just remember it unzips big to help remove them more easily.
customer_reviews.author: Chris Moran

customer_reviews.title: Not Worth Purchase
customer_reviews.text: Cheap plastic. The discs also barely differ from putter, mid, and driver. It’s worth paying a few more bucks to get a better disc set.
customer_reviews.author: ddbrown83

customer_reviews.title: Recieved 6 drivers and 3 midrange?
customer_reviews.text: Not as advertised. Do not match the photos. The Blue and Red discs are identical, and seem to be drivers. I got 3 Red drivers, 3 Blue drivers, and 3 Yellow midrange. NO putters? Or the 3 yellows are putters and I didn't get any midrange. But they don't look like the putters in the photos.
customer_reviews.author: Zachary Sturbaum

customer_reviews.title: I wish they stamped on the frisbee the flying characteristics ...
customer_reviews.text: I wish they stamped on the frisbee the flying characteristics. That would be helpful. The driver has quite a bit of Fade to it but as a new player, I don't know how much it's related just looking at it.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer K.

customer_reviews.title: Lower quality than expected
customer_reviews.text: Work okay but you get three drivers that look alike. Same with mid-range and putters. Need to give them to the kids for an art project. Rather stiff lower quality material not what you would normally expect. But they work to teach new people.
customer_reviews.author: Kindle Customer

customer_reviews.title: One disc came flat (damaged and unusable)
customer_reviews.text: I like the product, but one disc (orange) came flat in the package of 9 discs.
customer_reviews.author: Adas

customer_reviews.title: Great discs
customer_reviews.text: Great discs. Great way to learn without all the confusing pictures & numbers on the discs. I like the simplicity of them & the weight & feel are spot on. The bag tore at the top seam after a couple uses, but I am pretty hard on my bags.
customer_reviews.author: Pamcakes

customer_reviews.title: Excellent value for the money
customer_reviews.text: Good job here, the discs are boring to look at, but easily modified for looks. I get adequate distance from the driver, and the putter is accurate. Excellent value for the money
customer_reviews.author: Robert D. Wanless

customer_reviews.title: Great package for 3 golfers
customer_reviews.text: This is a great and convenient way for 3 of us to play disc golf. High quality and very nice construction. The travel bag makes it easy to bring all the discs with us when we go for a round.
customer_reviews.author: Nick A Kelly

customer_reviews.title: Overall not bad quality for beginners
customer_reviews.text: Overall not bad quality for beginners. My boyfriend and I just bought this set. It's a great price and we have an extra set for a friend. The discs have gotten a lot of use lately. The only thing I am hating about this sport is the ticks in the high grass... yikes :(
customer_reviews.author: Abby

customer_reviews.title: For Beginners
customer_reviews.text: These are great for beginners wanting to learn, or friends that want to goof around on a disc golf course. Certainly not recommended for people who are wanting to become great at this sport. There are no ratings on them, so they can not be compared to other brands/models. Decent quality, slightly heavy, and they have HORRIBLE fade, but they are good for beginners.
customer_reviews.author: JC

customer_reviews.title: I enjoyed playing so much I have moved beyond them
customer_reviews.text: Bought these to take the family to disc golf. If you have never played these are alright. I enjoyed playing so much I have moved beyond them. Great for the wife to play with though.
customer_reviews.author: Bud Dogood

customer_reviews.title: $30 to get you and two other people to explore Frisbee golf. Can't go wrong.
customer_reviews.text: This is a great way to explore the fun of Frisbee golf. I have only played a couple of times but have improved each time I went out.
customer_reviews.author: Stevie Ray.

customer_reviews.title: They work like frisbees.
customer_reviews.text: What can I say, they are flying discs. We're not pros, but they work fine for us.
customer_reviews.author: Blake L.

customer_reviews.title: Great starter set.
customer_reviews.text: Got this for my son's birthday. It's great because it has 3 sets so he and his friends or brother can go play together without having to borrow discs from others. Great starter set.
customer_reviews.author: Denise

customer_reviews.title: Great buy
customer_reviews.text: Love the discs and bag they come in is great!
customer_reviews.author: lee ann garton

customer_reviews.title: Seems good
customer_reviews.text: Seems very practical and reasonable quality haven't used them yet, darn weather!
customer_reviews.author: Bill in MD

customer_reviews.title: Good set to get introduced to the game
customer_reviews.text: Don't fly as well as the more expensive discs, but perfect for beginners who are just getting introduced to the game.
customer_reviews.author: Jason Tran

customer_reviews.title: Good value
customer_reviews.text: Decent for the price. They got fairly scuffed up after one round, but again, well worth the price
customer_reviews.author: kim

customer_reviews.title: Had lots of fun using this set
customer_reviews.text: Had lots of fun using this set. New to disk golf, but lots of experience with ultimate. Could never control the yellow disks very well, used mostly the blue and red disks.
customer_reviews.author: Salty Dog

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Great inexpensive fun for my family! Well worth the price and shipping was very speedy!
customer_reviews.author: kristin

customer_reviews.title: Four Stars
customer_reviews.text: Great for beginners. Blue is short (putt), orange is mid-range, yellow is long range.
customer_reviews.author: Gidgiddoni

customer_reviews.title: ... a course for first time beginners and they worked great. There are three sets of each
customer_reviews.text: Bought these to go disc golf on a course for first time beginners and they worked great. There are three sets of each. The disc held up well and flew as we expected. A great for the price.
customer_reviews.author: Iowa Home

customer_reviews.title: Family Disc Golf Time
customer_reviews.text: This set is exactly what was needed. Yes some of the discs got marked up the first use, but at $4 per disc what can you expect. I was looking for sets that my children could use to allow us to play as a family. This was perfect. Who wants to put a $20 disc in a 7 year old's hand - especially in a wooded and rocky course. None of the discs broke and we have used them a few times. We will continue to do so until my girls are old enough and good enough to benefit from higher end discs.
customer_reviews.author: Melson5

customer_reviews.title: but great for kids
customer_reviews.text: Decent for the price. Not for use for serious disc golf players, but great for kids.
customer_reviews.author: Melissa

customer_reviews.title: Great for family
customer_reviews.text: Great way to start with the family. Customized with sharpie to make 3 different sets
customer_reviews.author: Peter Kedl

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Excellent, exactly what I was looking for at a great price too.
customer_reviews.author: William E Weeks

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: kids had great time with these discs and they were able to share them with their friends & cousins.
customer_reviews.author: Vickster

customer_reviews.title: Not bad
customer_reviews.text: This is actually a pretty decent set of discs here. I'm not to fond of the driver but, my buddy was launching it pretty far. I am very impressed with the mid range and especially the driver. I was a little skeptical because the drivers are a tiny bit lopsided, but they fly so straight. I was busting long putts left and right. This is a great beginner set.
customer_reviews.author: Savbeast916

customer_reviews.title: Three Stars
customer_reviews.text: Because of the price this is a good deal, but the discs get banged up very easy.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: Order was on time and product was exactly what i wanted
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Disks are not labeled, there are no indicators for ...
customer_reviews.text: Disks are not labeled, there are no indicators for which is which, the price is cheap though so these will be spares in case i want to bring friends that do not have their own set.
customer_reviews.author: Ross

customer_reviews.title: Think these were received in good order= they were both sent as gifts= for grandchildren ...
customer_reviews.text: Think these were received in good order= they were both sent as gifts= for grandchildren and nephews- have not heard any bad reviews
customer_reviews.author: Maggie O

customer_reviews.title: Great set at a great value for a large family!
customer_reviews.text: This is a great set and a great value for novice players. We are foster parents and currently have 4 teenagers in our family so disc golf is a fun experience for the entire family. This set came in handy when one of our kids requested a disc golf adventure for his birthday and we realized additional children would be involved. The set was affordable enough for us to provide sets for everyone that attended. The only thing that would make them better would be for them to have some kind of labels to identify them as individual sets but we easily solved that with a sharpie.
customer_reviews.author: E. Lioret

customer_reviews.title: Warped discs.
customer_reviews.text: All of the smaller discs are warped and do not throw well. Very bad.
customer_reviews.author: DmsaaMN

customer_reviews.title: Keep it in your trunk!
customer_reviews.text: Nice beginner sets to carry around for when you talk friends into/take kids disc golfing for the first time without having to sacrifice your good discs! The mid-range is a particularly decent
customer_reviews.author: S. Yager

product_meta.title: Trademark Innovations Disc Golf Set (9 Discs) with Disc Golf Bag
product_meta.description: This set of golf discs includes 9 discs (3) drivers, (3) mid-range discs and (3) putters. Disc driver specs (yellow discs): speed 9, glide 5 , turn -3 , fade 1. Mid- range specs (orange discs): speed 4, glide 4, 0 turn, 3 fade. Putter specs (blue discs): speed 2, glide 3, turn 0, 2 fade. Great starter set for someone wanting to learn the game. By Trademark Innovations.
